05/08/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A service in memory of the victims of Croatia's military Operation Storm was held at St Marko's Church in Belgrade on Wednesday (August 4th). 
President Boris Tadic and other politicians were in attendance. 
About 2,000 Serbs were killed or went missing during the operation launched on August 4th 1995, while another 200,000 Serb civilians living in Croatia fled to Serbia. 
Bosnian Serbs also commemorated the anniversary. 
(RTS, Tanjug, RTRS, Politika - 04/08/10)
